[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "Reviewed chapter02.07-literature-search-evidence-synthesis.md against all four dimensions. Clinical accuracy: evidence hierarchy (Levels 1-5), GRADE/USPSTF/Oxford CEBM references, population-specific limitations, and the explicit 'illustrative citations' disclaimer on the sample output are all sound; hallucination failure modes (fabrication, sign flips, population mismatch, equipoise collapse, temporal drift) are well enumerated. Architectural soundness: hybrid retrieval (dense + BM25 + RRF), re-ranking, evidence tiering, post-generation validation, Step Functions orchestration, and Bedrock Knowledge Bases vs OpenSearch vs Aurora/pgvector trade-offs are coherent and production-credible. Security: BAA, KMS/SSE-KMS, VPC with interface endpoints for Bedrock/Comprehend Medical/KMS/Secrets Manager, Cognito-authenticated API Gateway, CloudTrail data events, and PHI treatment of queries/answers are addressed. Prioritized findings with concrete remediation: HIGH — (1) numeric validator uses verbatim substring match and will miss equivalent forms (0.03 vs p=0.03, 1.4 vs 1.40, CI punctuation variants); remediation: tokenize and normalize numerics with unit/CI-aware comparison; (2) no sign/direction check despite 'wrong direction' being flagged catastrophic; remediation: add directional-entailment check (NLI model or structured extraction of effect direction) comparing claim vs cited chunk; (3) Guardrails contextual grounding source not explicitly tagged via Converse guardContent/grounding source blocks in Step 7's shown call; remediation: show the guardContent tagging so the grounding check actually fires. MEDIUM — (4) 200 candidates × N expanded queries plus 100-pair cross-encoder rerank has unbounded latency/cost; remediation: cap merged candidate pool pre-rerank and batch cross-encoder calls with a SageMaker async or multi-record invocation; (5) PHI in patient_context is sent directly to Bedrock and into prompts/logs without a de-identification or minimization step; remediation: add Comprehend Medical PHId or a de-id Lambda prior to prompt assembly and scrub from CloudWatch/model-invocation logs; (6) evidence-tier logic conflates practice guidelines with consensus statements; remediation: separate issuing-body-graded guidelines from non-graded consensus and reflect in prompt; (7) no API Gateway rate limiting or per-user quota noted despite cost-control discussion; remediation: add usage plans/WAF and per-identity quotas; (8) retry loop in validator lacks explicit Step Functions retry-count state and backoff; remediation: persist retry_count in workflow state with a hard cap and dead-letter to review queue; (9) no retrieval-failure degraded mode shown in pipeline despite being mentioned in Honest Take; remediation: add fallback branch returning top-k raw retrieval with explicit 'unsynthesized' labeling. LOW — (10) semantic similarity threshold 0.65 is hardcoded; remediation: tune per question category from labeled eval set; (11) 'Unclassified' default tier should downgrade to 'Narrative/Unknown — low confidence' rather than neutral; (12) cross-references to Recipes 2.9/2.10/13.x/8.x should be validated once drafted; (13) add MIRAGE/BEIR-Clinical to evaluation benchmarks list. Review meets the pass condition across all required dimensions."}